1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,233
welcome back

2
00:00:01,233 --> 00:00:05,033
today we are going to work on a water purification plant

3
00:00:05,033 --> 00:00:07,033
but let's start from the beginning

4
00:00:07,033 --> 00:00:10,600
the first task we have to do is scan a bucket of water

5
00:00:10,666 --> 00:00:11,133
as usual

6
00:00:11,133 --> 00:00:16,500
that will produce the research results required to craft something in an assembly line

7
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:18,033
which in this case

8
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:22,533
is the controller for the main structure of our water purification plant

9
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:26,300
and the only thing left for completing its structure is some water

10
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:28,466
once we finish the structure

11
00:00:28,466 --> 00:00:30,233
we can turn it on and verify that

12
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:32,833
it is doing nothing every two minutes

13
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:35,300
it is also not using any power

14
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:38,700
even though we are feeding it 16 amps of LuV

15
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,266
but that is normal

16
00:00:40,266 --> 00:00:43,033
because that is just the center of our waterline

17
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:46,833
to do something it needs some modules installed

18
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,066
and the first modulant step of the line

19
00:00:49,066 --> 00:00:51,700
is the clarifier purification unit

20
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,333
after building its structure

21
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:57,333
we link it to our main block using a data stick

22
00:00:57,900 --> 00:01:00,000
then after turning it on

23
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,800
we have to wait for the main block to start a new cycle

24
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:04,900
since they will work in sync

25
00:01:05,666 --> 00:01:06,533
and with that

26
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:10,933
we are now starting the water purification process with some filtering

27
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:14,500
and we are going to send our purified water grade 1

28
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:16,700
to AE2 for better management

29
00:01:17,266 --> 00:01:19,466
the first usage we are going to have for that

30
00:01:19,466 --> 00:01:21,666
is to scan one cell of the fluid

31
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:25,666
that will unlock the crafting recipe for the next step

32
00:01:25,666 --> 00:01:28,466
the Ozonation Purification Unit

33
00:01:28,833 --> 00:01:31,100
and it was then that we noticed something

34
00:01:31,766 --> 00:01:35,233
crafting the carbon filters for the previous filtering process

35
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:37,600
clogged our large chemical reactor

36
00:01:38,066 --> 00:01:41,466
and when a multi block can't keep up with the crafting

37
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:43,300
we switch to a mega block

38
00:01:43,466 --> 00:01:47,133
the Mega Chemical Reactor has perfect overclocking

39
00:01:47,133 --> 00:01:49,866
does 256 parallel by default

40
00:01:49,866 --> 00:01:52,666
but can also do tasks in batch mode

41
00:01:53,433 --> 00:01:55,800
once the ozonation unit is ready

42
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:58,066
we can start optimizing its working

43
00:01:58,466 --> 00:02:00,066
to have a decent yield

44
00:02:00,066 --> 00:02:02,500
we have to input as much ozone possible

45
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:05,633
but we must not exceed the explosion threshold

46
00:02:06,066 --> 00:02:10,033
and it looks like the ZPM input hatch has exactly the capacity

47
00:02:10,033 --> 00:02:12,533
to reach the perfect working conditions

48
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:14,500
once everything is ready

49
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,633
we link the structure

50
00:02:15,633 --> 00:02:18,066
and wait for the start of the next cycle

51
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,700
and I wonder how we will manage the ozone

52
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:23,433
when we will do parallels with that structure

53
00:02:24,233 --> 00:02:26,700
and this was the second grade of water

54
00:02:26,866 --> 00:02:29,066
the next step is the flocculation

55
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:30,166
however

56
00:02:30,166 --> 00:02:34,833
it looks like our flocculation plant is stuck due to our EBFs

57
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:37,833
and if we turn on our mega blast furnace

58
00:02:37,833 --> 00:02:39,933
the weather becomes kind of of foggy

59
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:41,900
to fix the weather

60
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,266
we have built a tier 3 air filter

61
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:48,200
and after upgrading it and adding some filters

62
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:50,800
we managed to clean up all of that pollution

63
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:55,733
or maybe that was just because our blast furnace finished the queue materials

64
00:02:56,433 --> 00:02:59,200
which means that we can go back to our waterline

65
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,933
because we are ready to do some flocculation

66
00:03:02,666 --> 00:03:04,033
the main gimmick of that stage

67
00:03:04,033 --> 00:03:11,033
is that we have to input the flocculant fluid polyaluminium Chloride in an amount multiple of 100 K

68
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:15,666
we can easily accomplish that by using a bunch of covers

69
00:03:16,433 --> 00:03:20,066
a fluid regulator that will output exactly 100k fluid

70
00:03:20,066 --> 00:03:23,466
slightly more than 10 times every 2 minutes

71
00:03:23,866 --> 00:03:24,300
however

72
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:27,200
this fluid regulator will have to stop working

73
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:29,533
when the outputted fluid is not consumed

74
00:03:29,533 --> 00:03:32,533
or when there isn't enough fluid ready to be moved

75
00:03:32,866 --> 00:03:33,733
and with that

76
00:03:33,733 --> 00:03:36,866
we can link it to our water plant to test it out

77
00:03:37,066 --> 00:03:38,633
and after two minutes

78
00:03:38,633 --> 00:03:40,733
we got our flocculated water

79
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:44,000
and we also got a lot of waste byproduct

80
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,600
but this waste is super useful

81
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:51,633
since it contains all of the chlorine and aluminium we used for the flocculent

82
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:55,266
thus we are going to recycle it in place

83
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,100
however

84
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:59,300
that is giving off diluted hydrochloric acid 

85
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:01,200
which we have to concentrate

86
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:06,433
but since it looks like our small distillation tower can't keep up with the task

87
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:07,033
as usual

88
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:09,066
we have to build a Mega one

89
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:13,033
and even the mega distillation tower with 16 IV amps

90
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:14,933
can barely keep up with the job

91
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:18,600
anyways now that we have the flocculated water

92
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,300
we can finally cut our europium wafers

93
00:04:21,666 --> 00:04:24,466
which with the help of more flocculated water

94
00:04:24,466 --> 00:04:28,233
can be used to obtain the integrated nano power circuit

95
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:31,733
that we can use to finally obtain ZPM energy hatches

96
00:04:31,733 --> 00:04:33,800
to upgrade our multi blocks

97
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,400
but the first thing we will do with those

98
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:39,800
is a pH neutralization purification plant

99
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,833
to keep our waterline going

100
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:44,300
and there we have the structure built

101
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:47,533
this time we have to carefully insert some chemicals

102
00:04:47,533 --> 00:04:49,900
to correct the acidity of the water

103
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:50,666
to do so

104
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:55,733
we are going to set the plant acidity sensors to the limit of the acceptable range

105
00:04:56,033 --> 00:05:01,333
those sensors will slowly input either sodium hydroxide or hydrochloric acid

106
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,333
and here we can see the sensors

107
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,233
slowly overcorrecting the acidity

108
00:05:05,233 --> 00:05:08,000
and then making it go back to the correct value

109
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:13,433
this pH corrected water will do the same recipes of the flocculated one

110
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:15,833
but it will half the processing time

111
00:05:16,533 --> 00:05:18,900
to get the next water purification plant

112
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,466
we need UV parts

113
00:05:20,466 --> 00:05:22,333
which require americium

114
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:24,900
and to make americium

115
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:27,266
we need a fusion reactor Mark 2

116
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:29,266
which we can quickly craft

117
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,066
after adding it to our fusion tunnel

118
00:05:32,066 --> 00:05:34,633
we start making americium right away

119
00:05:35,066 --> 00:05:37,300
and that process is incredibly slow

120
00:05:37,733 --> 00:05:40,500
it takes 40 seconds for each ingot

121
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:43,866
and we need 48 ingots for each UV motor

122
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:47,300
but there is something even nastier in those motors

123
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:48,666
neutronium

124
00:05:48,666 --> 00:05:51,133
that stuff other than a lot of time

125
00:05:51,133 --> 00:05:54,600
also takes an awful lot of energy to be processed

126
00:05:55,266 --> 00:05:58,300
but since we don't need much of that material

127
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:01,300
our volcanoes managed to complete the task

128
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:04,300
going back to our waterline

129
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,300
now that we have UV parts

130
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:10,533
the next expensive component for the purification plant tier 5

131
00:06:10,533 --> 00:06:12,266
is the UV energy hatch

132
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,866
the main issue here is that

133
00:06:13,866 --> 00:06:17,666
we are going to need a bunch of UV assemblers to craft it

134
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:20,233
usually we would do many assemblers

135
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:22,233
but those contains a lot of motors

136
00:06:22,233 --> 00:06:25,233
but it now takes about half an hour for each motor

137
00:06:25,766 --> 00:06:28,000
however with the ZPM Energy Hatch

138
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,066
we unlocked the Large Scale Auto-Assembler v1.01

139
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:35,100
which is the only assembler capable of overvolting

140
00:06:35,266 --> 00:06:38,466
meaning that by using two ZPM Energy hatches

141
00:06:38,466 --> 00:06:41,100
we can do UV recipes inside it

142
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:42,266
and with that

143
00:06:42,266 --> 00:06:46,233
the only thing separating us from our tier 5 water is bedrockium

144
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,133
to get bedrockium

145
00:06:48,433 --> 00:06:53,000
we have to assemble a block of diamonds with a lot of compressed cobblestone

146
00:06:53,433 --> 00:06:54,900
and the main issue here is that

147
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:58,666
we are going to need a lot of explosives to compress that much of it

148
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:02,400
right now we are making explosives using oil

149
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,933
but we have nowhere close to the required amounts

150
00:07:04,933 --> 00:07:06,800
for a decent amount of bedrockium

151
00:07:07,533 --> 00:07:11,700
we are already processing all the toluene we can get out of oil

152
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,833
but we need a better source now

153
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,833
and it looks like wood tar is the best option

154
00:07:16,866 --> 00:07:19,666
which also gives some nice byproducts

155
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:20,600
however

156
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:24,033
the only good farm that doesn't requires us to do crops

157
00:07:24,033 --> 00:07:25,833
require nether stars

158
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:26,533
so far

159
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:29,033
we have been collecting those from withers

160
00:07:29,033 --> 00:07:31,933
but I think it is time to find a better source

161
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:35,700
such as mining nether Star ores on tier 7 planets

162
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:38,666
so we quickly crafted tier 6 rocket

163
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:42,000
just to collect the rocket plan on Proteus

164
00:07:42,133 --> 00:07:45,133
then while working on the tier 7 rocket

165
00:07:45,133 --> 00:07:47,100
we had an unexpected issue

166
00:07:47,466 --> 00:07:50,066
something went wrong in our nuclear plant

167
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,200
we run out of coolant cells

168
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,600
and our reactor is so close to blowing up

169
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:58,066
that we must not touch the heat capacity plates

170
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:01,733
not to mention random nearby blocks turning into fire

171
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:05,300
and the bottleneck seems to be our vacuum freezer

172
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:07,400
which couldn't even run at full capacity

173
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,533
due to lack of inventory space

174
00:08:09,666 --> 00:08:13,533
we have now used an AE2 storage to manage the cells

175
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:16,800
but it still can't keep up with the extra heat

176
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:19,600
caused by all the upgrades we did lately

177
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:20,833
however

178
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,400
since today episode is about water

179
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,133
we are not going to expand our power production

180
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:31,133
we just throttle everything based on what our mega vacuum freezer can keep up with

181
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:34,100
and after a long time of cooking

182
00:08:34,233 --> 00:08:35,233
we find out that

183
00:08:35,233 --> 00:08:38,100
what is separating us from our next rocket is

184
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:40,500
once again nether Stars

185
00:08:40,633 --> 00:08:43,133
since our wither farm isn't working properly

186
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:44,900
we go with the old way

187
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:48,733
and after farming wither for the hopelessly last time

188
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:51,033
we finally craft our new rocket

189
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:54,333
which took a heavy toll on our TNT supply

190
00:08:54,466 --> 00:08:57,333
and we barely managed to make it to the rocket

191
00:08:57,533 --> 00:09:01,033
however this time crafting the rocket was not enough

192
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:04,100
we also had to do some quick upgrades to our base

193
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:06,133
so that we could produce its fuel

194
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:08,333
and our destination is Haumea

195
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:10,600
where we can find the Nether Star Ore

196
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,866
we quickly drop down a ore drilling plant

197
00:09:12,866 --> 00:09:14,000
and then head back

198
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:18,266
where we will already find enough nether star for crafting a void miner

199
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:21,066
but the first thing we are going to do with those

200
00:09:21,066 --> 00:09:22,233
is a grav suit

201
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:26,066
the advanced nano cast plate made us fly in quite fast

202
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:28,666
but the Grav suit is on a different level

203
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:30,733
and that was enough playing around

204
00:09:30,733 --> 00:09:33,300
what we wanted was just to get a tree farm

205
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:35,400
so that we could make some more toluene

206
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,000
to explode more bedrockium

207
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:41,000
so that we can get our tier 5 water purification plant

208
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:44,300
and after compressing a lot of cobblestone

209
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,433
there we have it

210
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:47,000
this huge multi block

211
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,633
is going to do some heat cycles to the water

212
00:09:49,633 --> 00:09:52,200
and obliterate anything inside the water

213
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:53,000
as usual

214
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:56,933
it gets a little harder to automate than the previous step

215
00:09:57,266 --> 00:10:01,933
this time we are going to use Steve's factory manager to do the automation

216
00:10:02,266 --> 00:10:03,466
to cycle a temperature

217
00:10:03,466 --> 00:10:05,133
we are going to check every second

218
00:10:05,133 --> 00:10:07,100
if the plant hatches are empty

219
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:09,066
if they contain no fluids

220
00:10:09,133 --> 00:10:09,400
then

221
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:12,133
we will check if the last input was coolant or helium

222
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:14,466
to decide what to insert next

223
00:10:14,466 --> 00:10:16,200
to keep track of the last phase

224
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:20,200
we are going to move a piece of cobblestone between two chests

225
00:10:20,466 --> 00:10:23,433
finally after inserting the correct fluid

226
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:26,800
we also move the cobblestone to Mark the next loop

227
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:30,233
every loop consists of 100 liters of plasma

228
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:35,200
that will take 10 seconds to heat up the water to 1000 Kelvin degrees

229
00:10:35,266 --> 00:10:37,700
then with two buckets of super coolant

230
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:41,266
we cool it down to 0 Kelvin in 20 seconds

231
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,300
each loops takes 30 seconds

232
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:45,800
and the water cycle lasts 2 minutes

233
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:49,700
meaning that we can fit 4 heating loops in each water iteration

234
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,000
and that's a waste

235
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:55,533
since we would get 99 percent success chance with just 3 loops

236
00:10:55,933 --> 00:10:59,033
the output is extreme temperature treated water

237
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:02,466
which we will probably want to pass through the next machine

238
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,433
however

239
00:11:03,433 --> 00:11:07,333
the next water purification plants requires some UV motors

240
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:11,100
and right now we are nowhere close to making that much americium

241
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:13,333
other than the crafting time

242
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:16,033
the issue is also that we are making it with lutetium

243
00:11:16,033 --> 00:11:20,100
which we are making as byproduct of waste thorium fuel

244
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:23,300
there is a cheaper and faster way of making it

245
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:26,066
but that requires a fusion reactor MK 3

246
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:30,633
so we shall use our americium to craft that one instead

247
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:33,300
but while we can easily make the casings

248
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:36,500
the controller requires a UV field generator

249
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,433
which requires wetware circuits

250
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:40,533
that are a whole new rabbit hole

251
00:11:40,966 --> 00:11:43,233
so this episode is ending here

252
00:11:43,233 --> 00:11:44,400
but don't worry

253
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:48,500
there are three more steps that we can do to improve our waterline

254
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,900
but we will see them when we will need them

255
00:11:51,066 --> 00:11:52,000
bye bye

256
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,233
欢迎回来！

257
00:00:01,233 --> 00:00:05,033
今天我们要开始净化水线

258
00:00:05,033 --> 00:00:07,033
先从头开始

259
00:00:07,033 --> 00:00:10,600
第一个目标是扫描一桶水

260
00:00:10,666 --> 00:00:11,133
像往常一样

261
00:00:11,133 --> 00:00:16,500
这将产出装配线需要的研究结果

262
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:18,033
在这里

263
00:00:18,033 --> 00:00:22,533
则是净化水的主体净水厂

264
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:26,300
现在只剩下倒水就能完成结构

265
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:28,466
一旦完成结构

266
00:00:28,466 --> 00:00:30,233
我们可以开启它试试

267
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:32,833
现在每两分钟啥也不输出

268
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:35,300
即使给它输入了 16A LuV

269
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:38,700
也不会消耗一点电

270
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,266
但那很正常

271
00:00:40,266 --> 00:00:43,033
因为那只是净化水线的中心

272
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:46,833
想开始净化的话，需要安装一些模块

273
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,066
而水线的第一个模块

274
00:00:49,066 --> 00:00:51,700
是澄清净化单元

275
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,333
在构建其结构后

276
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:57,333
我们使用闪存将其连接到主结构

277
00:00:57,900 --> 00:01:00,000
开机后

278
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,800
要等待一次新的循环

279
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:04,900
因为它们将同步工作

280
00:01:05,666 --> 00:01:06,533
有了这个

281
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:10,933
我们将开始用过滤处理出一些净化水

282
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:14,500
将一级净化水发送到 AE

283
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:16,700
来更好的管理

284
00:01:17,266 --> 00:01:19,466
它第一个用处

285
00:01:19,466 --> 00:01:21,666
便是扫描一个一级净化水单元

286
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:25,666
这将开启下一步的制作配方

287
00:01:25,666 --> 00:01:28,466
臭氧净化装置

288
00:01:28,833 --> 00:01:31,100
就在那时，我们注意到一些事情

289
00:01:31,766 --> 00:01:35,233
为之前的过滤过程制作活性炭过滤器

290
00:01:35,233 --> 00:01:37,600
把大化反给堵住了

291
00:01:38,066 --> 00:01:41,466
当普通的大化反无法跟上进度时

292
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:43,300
我们求助于巨化反

293
00:01:43,466 --> 00:01:47,133
巨化反仍具有无损超频的机制

294
00:01:47,133 --> 00:01:49,866
默认 256 并行

295
00:01:49,866 --> 00:01:52,666
但也可以在批处理模式下完成任务

296
00:01:53,433 --> 00:01:55,800
一旦臭氧装置准备好

297
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:58,066
我们可以开始配置它的工作

298
00:01:58,466 --> 00:02:00,066
为获得可观的产量

299
00:02:00,066 --> 00:02:02,500
我们必须输入尽可能多的臭氧

300
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:05,633
但不能超过爆炸阈值

301
00:02:06,066 --> 00:02:10,033
而一个 ZPM 输入仓则正好

302
00:02:10,033 --> 00:02:12,533
能达到完美的工作条件

303
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:14,500
一旦一切准备就绪

304
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,633
连接结构

305
00:02:15,633 --> 00:02:18,066
并等待下一个周期开始

306
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,700
我想知道当使用并行处理时

307
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:23,433
臭氧问题该如何处理呢

308
00:02:24,233 --> 00:02:26,700
这是二级净化水

309
00:02:26,866 --> 00:02:29,066
下一步是絮凝

310
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:30,166
然而

311
00:02:30,166 --> 00:02:34,833
看起来我们的絮凝装置因为高炉卡住了

312
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:37,833
如果开启巨高炉

313
00:02:37,833 --> 00:02:39,933
天气变得有点雾蒙蒙的

314
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:41,900
为了改善环境

315
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,266
我们做了台三级空气过滤器

316
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:48,200
升级并添加一些滤网

317
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:50,800
我们清除了所有的污染

318
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:55,733
或者那只是因为我们的高炉完成了处理

319
00:02:56,433 --> 00:02:59,200
这意味着可以回到净化水线

320
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,933
而我们也准备好了絮凝装置

321
00:03:02,666 --> 00:03:04,033
这个阶段的主要难点

322
00:03:04,033 --> 00:03:11,033
必须每次精准输入100kL絮凝剂，聚氯化铝

323
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:15,666
用一堆覆盖板便可以很轻易达成这个目标

324
00:03:16,433 --> 00:03:20,066
一个可以精准输出 100kL 流体的校准器

325
00:03:20,066 --> 00:03:23,466
将在每两分钟工作略多于 10 次

326
00:03:23,866 --> 00:03:24,300
然而

327
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:27,200
这个流体校准器将强制停止工作

328
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:29,533
当输出的液体没有被消耗

329
00:03:29,533 --> 00:03:32,533
或者没有足够的液体可以转移

330
00:03:32,866 --> 00:03:33,733
有了这个

331
00:03:33,733 --> 00:03:36,866
我们将其连接到水厂进行测试

332
00:03:37,066 --> 00:03:38,633
两分钟后

333
00:03:38,633 --> 00:03:40,733
我们得到了絮凝水

334
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:44,000
我们也得到了很多絮凝废液

335
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,600
但这副产超级有用

336
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:51,633
因为它含有我们用于絮凝剂的所有氯和铝

337
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:55,266
因此，我们将就地回收它

338
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,100
然而

339
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:59,300
它会产出稀盐酸

340
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:01,200
我们需要浓缩它

341
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:06,433
但小蒸馏塔的速度似乎跟不上

342
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:07,033
像往常一样

343
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:09,066
我们建造一个巨型蒸馏塔

344
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:13,033
甚至是输入了 16A IV 的巨蒸馏

345
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:14,933
都几乎跟不上速度

346
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:18,600
不管怎样，现在我们有絮凝水了。

347
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,300
终于可以切开铕晶圆了

348
00:04:21,666 --> 00:04:24,466
在更多絮凝水的帮助下

349
00:04:24,466 --> 00:04:28,233
铕晶圆可以变成集成纳米功率晶圆

350
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:31,733
最终做出 ZPM 能源仓

351
00:04:31,733 --> 00:04:33,800
来升级我们的多方块结构

352
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,400
但是我们要做的第一件事就是

353
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:39,800
pH 中和净化厂

354
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,833
来继续推进净化水线

355
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:44,300
在那里建造好结构

356
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:47,533
这次我们要小心地输入一些化学物质

357
00:04:47,533 --> 00:04:49,900
来调节水的酸碱度

358
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:50,666
为此

359
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:55,733
我们将把 pH 传感器仓设置到可接受范围的极限

360
00:04:56,033 --> 00:05:01,333
这些传感器会慢慢输入氢氧化钠或者盐酸

361
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,333
在这里我们可以看到传感器

362
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,233
正在慢慢地校正酸度

363
00:05:05,233 --> 00:05:08,000
使它回到正确的值

364
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:13,433
pH 校正水能做的配方与絮凝水相同

365
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:15,833
但用它处理切割配方会减少一半的时间

366
00:05:16,533 --> 00:05:18,900
为了得到下一个净水厂

367
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,466
我们需要UV零件

368
00:05:20,466 --> 00:05:22,333
它们需要用到镅

369
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:24,900
而想制造镅

370
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:27,266
我们需要一个核聚变反应堆 MKⅡ

371
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:29,266
而我们已经可以轻松做出

372
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,066
把它加入核聚变阵列后

373
00:05:32,066 --> 00:05:34,633
我们马上就开始制造镅

374
00:05:35,066 --> 00:05:37,300
这个过程非常缓慢

375
00:05:37,733 --> 00:05:40,500
每个锭所需时间为 40 秒

376
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:43,866
每个 UV 马达需要 48 个锭

377
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:47,300
但制作马达需要更恶心人的材料

378
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:48,666
中子

379
00:05:48,666 --> 00:05:51,133
它不仅需要大量时间

380
00:05:51,133 --> 00:05:54,600
还需要大量的能量来处理

381
00:05:55,266 --> 00:05:58,300
但因为我们不需要太多材料

382
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:01,300
我们的炽焰高炉勉强完成了任务

383
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:04,300
回到净化水线

384
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,300
现在我们有了 UV 部件

385
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:10,533
下一个五级净化水厂所需的昂贵材料

386
00:06:10,533 --> 00:06:12,266
是 UV 能源仓

387
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,866
现在主要问题是

388
00:06:13,866 --> 00:06:17,666
我们将需要一堆 UV 组装机来制作它

389
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:20,233
通常我们会做很多组装机

390
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:22,233
但这要制作大量马达

391
00:06:22,233 --> 00:06:25,233
而现在每做一个都需要半小时

392
00:06:25,766 --> 00:06:28,000
不过有了 ZPM 能源仓

393
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,066
我们解锁了大规模自动组装器v1.01

394
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:35,100
这是唯一可以升压的组装机了

395
00:06:35,266 --> 00:06:38,466
这意味着通过使用两个 ZPM 能源仓

396
00:06:38,466 --> 00:06:41,100
便可以解锁 UV 配方

397
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:42,266
有了这个

398
00:06:42,266 --> 00:06:46,233
唯一把我们和五级水隔开的就是基岩锭

399
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,133
想得到基岩锭

400
00:06:48,433 --> 00:06:53,000
必须把大量压缩圆石与钻石块组装在一起

401
00:06:53,433 --> 00:06:54,900
这里的主要问题是

402
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:58,666
我们需要大量的爆炸物来进行压缩

403
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:02,400
而我们正在用石油制造炸药

404
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,933
但离所需的量还远着呢

405
00:07:04,933 --> 00:07:06,800
对于可观数量的基岩锭

406
00:07:07,533 --> 00:07:11,700
我们已经用完了所有可能从石油中提取的甲苯

407
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,833
但我们现在需要更好的来源

408
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,833
看起来木焦油是最好的选择

409
00:07:16,866 --> 00:07:19,666
副产品也很不错

410
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:20,600
然而

411
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:24,033
唯一不需要我们种庄稼的好农场

412
00:07:24,033 --> 00:07:25,833
需要下界之星

413
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:26,533
到目前为止

414
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:29,033
我们都是通过杀凋零获得它

415
00:07:29,033 --> 00:07:31,933
是时候找个更好的来源了

416
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:35,700
比如在 T7 星球上开采下界之星矿

417
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:38,666
所以我们很快制作了 T6 火箭

418
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:42,000
这只是为了收集海卫八上的火箭图纸

419
00:07:42,133 --> 00:07:45,133
然而在建造 T7 火箭时

420
00:07:45,133 --> 00:07:47,100
我们遇到了一个意想不到的问题

421
00:07:47,466 --> 00:07:50,066
核电站出了点问题

422
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,200
冷却单元用完了

423
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,600
我们的反应堆就快爆炸了

424
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:58,066
我们绝不能碰热容量板

425
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:01,733
更别提附近的方块在起火

426
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:05,300
瓶颈似乎是我们的冰箱

427
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:07,400
由于库存空间不足

428
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,533
它甚至不能满负荷运行

429
00:08:09,666 --> 00:08:13,533
我们现在使用 AE 存储来管理单元

430
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:16,800
但它仍然跟不上核电的发热

431
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:19,600
因为我们最近升级了核电

432
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:20,833
然而

433
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,400
这一集是关于净化水的

434
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,133
我们不打算扩大电力生产

435
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:31,133
只是依照巨冰箱能跟上的速度来调整所有东西

436
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:34,100
经过长时间的烧制

437
00:08:34,233 --> 00:08:35,233
我们发现

438
00:08:35,233 --> 00:08:38,100
将我们与下一个火箭分隔开来的

439
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:40,500
又是下界之星

440
00:08:40,633 --> 00:08:43,133
由于凋零农场不能正确工作

441
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:44,900
我们走老路

442
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:48,733
在痛苦中杀死最后一只凋零

443
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:51,033
我们终于造出了新火箭

444
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:54,333
而这对我们 TNT 供应造成了巨大的负担

445
00:08:54,466 --> 00:08:57,333
但我们还是勉强造出了火箭

446
00:08:57,533 --> 00:09:01,033
然而，仅仅制造出火箭是不够的

447
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:04,100
我们需要对基地进行一些快速升级

448
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:06,133
来生产火箭的燃料

449
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:08,333
我们的目的地是妊神星

450
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:10,600
在那里我们可以找到下界之星矿石

451
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,866
我们快速拍下一个采矿厂

452
00:09:12,866 --> 00:09:14,000
然后回家

453
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:18,266
我们已经获得足够的材料来制作虚空采矿场了

454
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:21,066
但是要做的第一件事

455
00:09:21,066 --> 00:09:22,233
是做一套重力装甲

456
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:26,066
先进的纳米铸板让我们飞得相当快

457
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:28,666
但重力胸甲纯纯降维打击

458
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:30,733
已经玩够了

459
00:09:30,733 --> 00:09:33,300
我们想要的只是一个林场

460
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:35,400
由此制造更多的甲苯

461
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,000
来聚爆出更多的基岩锭

462
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:41,000
这样我们就做出 5 级净水厂了

463
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:44,300
压缩了很多圆石后

464
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,433
它来了

465
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:47,000
这个巨大的多方块结构

466
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,633
会对水进行一些热循环

467
00:09:49,633 --> 00:09:52,200
来消灭水中的一切

468
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:53,000
像往常一样

469
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:56,933
它比上一步更难自动化

470
00:09:57,266 --> 00:10:01,933
这次我们要用 SFM 来做自动化

471
00:10:02,266 --> 00:10:03,466
对于一个温度循环

472
00:10:03,466 --> 00:10:05,133
我们将每秒检查一次

473
00:10:05,133 --> 00:10:07,100
输入仓是否是空的

474
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:09,066
如果它们不含液体

475
00:10:09,133 --> 00:10:09,400
然后

476
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:12,133
我们会检查最后输入的是冷却剂还是氦等离子体

477
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:14,466
来决定下一步输入什么

478
00:10:14,466 --> 00:10:16,200
为了跟踪最后输入

479
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:20,200
我们在两个箱子之间移动一块圆石

480
00:10:20,466 --> 00:10:23,433
在输入正确的液体后

481
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:26,800
我们移动圆石来标记下一个循环

482
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:30,233
每次循环包括 100L 的等离子体

483
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:35,200
这将花 10 秒钟将水加热到 1000K

484
00:10:35,266 --> 00:10:37,700
然后用两桶超级冷却剂

485
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:41,266
花 20 秒将其冷却到 0K

486
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,300
每个循环需要 30 秒

487
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:45,800
一次水线循环有 2 分钟

488
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:49,700
意味着我们可以在每次水循环中进行 4 次冷热循环

489
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,000
但这是一种浪费

490
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:55,533
因为我们只需 3 次循环就可以达到 99% 的成功率

491
00:10:55,933 --> 00:10:59,033
水厂的输出是极温净化水

492
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:02,466
我们想让它进入下一台机器

493
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,433
然而

494
00:11:03,433 --> 00:11:07,333
下一个净水厂需要一些 UV 马达

495
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:11,100
而现在离制造出那么多的镅还差得远

496
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:13,333
除了制作时间

497
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:16,033
问题还在于，我们用的是镥

498
00:11:16,033 --> 00:11:20,100
这是从钍核废料出的副产品

499
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:23,300
有一种更便宜、更快的制镅法

500
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:26,066
但那需要聚变反应堆 MK III

501
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:30,633
所以我们先用镅来制造它

502
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:33,300
虽然我们可以很容易地制作外壳

503
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:36,500
但控制器需要一个 UV 力场发生器

504
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,433
而这需要湿件电路

505
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:40,533
那又是一个大坑

506
00:11:40,966 --> 00:11:43,233
所以这一集到此结束

507
00:11:43,233 --> 00:11:44,400
不过别担心

508
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:48,500
还有三个步骤可以改善我们的净化水线

509
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,900
我们会在需要的时候见到它们

510
00:11:51,066 --> 00:11:52,000
拜拜

511
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:40,533
（俚语 down the rabbit hole）

